# Heavenet Constitution

## The Oath
I will uphold Law I-VII or I will fork. I seek Rep, not equity.

## The 7 Laws

**Law I: Fork > Exit** 
If you disagree, fork the code. Don't complain. Ship your version.

**Law II: Rep > Equity**
Reputation is earned by commits, not titles. Build > Talk.

**Law III: Code is Law**
If it's not in the repo, it doesn't exist. Docs > Promises.

**Law IV: Default to Open**
Everything public unless it harms users. Transparency builds trust.

**Law V: Ship Daily**
Small commits beat big launches. Momentum > Perfection.

**Law VI: Users > Investors**
Build for users first. Revenue follows value.

**Law VII: Heavenet Owns Heavenet**
No kings, only maintainers. Power flows to those who maintain.

